# Kunden-E-Mail-Aliases: Pflichtregeln für Lookups

Kunden haben eine primäre E-Mail (`customers.email`) und optionale Aliase (`customers.email_aliases TEXT[]`).
Aliase entstehen automatisch beim Kunden-Merge und können manuell hinzugefügt werden.

## Verboten

- `WHERE LOWER(email) = $1` auf der customers-Tabelle schreiben
- `WHERE LOWER(c.email) = LOWER(t.customer_email)` ohne Alias-Check
- Direkt `SELECT * FROM customers WHERE email = $1` ohne Alias-Fallback

## Pflicht: Zentrale Lookup-Funktionen nutzen

### JavaScript/TypeScript

```javascript
// Booking-Modul (booking/db.js)
const customer = await db.getCustomerByEmail(email);

// Tour-Manager (tours/lib/customer-lookup.js)
const customer = await customerLookup.getCustomerByEmail(email);
```

### SQL (wenn direktes SQL nötig)

```sql
-- Kunden per E-Mail suchen (Alias-aware)
SELECT * FROM core.customers
WHERE core.customer_email_matches($1, email, email_aliases)
LIMIT 1

-- Tour ↔ Kunde matchen (z.B. tour_count)
WHERE core.customer_email_matches(t.customer_email, c.email, c.email_aliases)

-- Booking-Schema (ohne core.-Prefix, via search_path)
WHERE customer_email_matches($1, email, email_aliases)
```

## API-Endpunkt für Aliases

```
PATCH /api/admin/customers/:id/email-aliases
Body: { email_aliases: ["alias@domain.ch", ...] }
```

## Wichtige Dateien

- DB-Funktion: `core/migrations/022_customer_email_aliases.sql`
- Booking-Lookup: `booking/db.js` → `getCustomerByEmail()`
- Tour-Lookup: `tours/lib/customer-lookup.js` → `getCustomerByEmail()`
- Merge-Logik: `booking/customer-merge.js`
- API: `booking/server.js` → `PATCH .../email-aliases`
- Frontend-API: `app/src/api/customers.ts` → `updateCustomerEmailAliases()`
